{"company_name": "nab-innovation-centre-vietnam", "job_name": "Senior/Lead Android Engineer (Java, Kotlin)", "tag_list": "\nAndroid\n\n\nKotlin\n\n\nJava\n", "location": "E. Town Central, 11 Doan Van Bo, District 4, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Very competitive remuneration package\nBuild products for millions of users in Australia\nHybrid and flexible working environment", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>We're seeking experienced and talented Mobile Engineers to work on our flagship mobile platform that serves millions of customers daily</strong>.</p><p>As a <strong>Senior/Lead</strong> <strong>Android Engineer</strong>, you'll join other Engineers, Manager Engineers, Test Automation Engineers, Business Analysts, and UX Designers. You’ll own key modules of our global product where you’ll use and grow your experience to architect and build mobile applications to maintain high availability and reliability. </p><p><strong>YOUR JOB RESPONSIBILITIES </strong></p><ol>\n<li>Provide hands-on leadership to the design, development, and deployment of technical solutions;</li>\n<li>Collaborate with other NAB's technology leaders towards improving and fulfilling the NAB technical direction;</li>\n<li>Design, develop, review, implement, and manage application code and services for the production and pre-release environments;</li>\n<li>Design, develop, review, implement and manage continuous integration, build management and deployment scripts, systems, and any code as required;</li>\n<li>Participate in Agile software development, prototyping, and code review with international development teams to build mobile apps;</li>\n<li>Understand the requirements of the customer or business and utilize this knowledge to develop applications that are consistent;</li>\n<li>Monitors for and anticipates platform trends and upcoming critical changes;</li>\n<li>Monitors client feedback for problems and proactively schedules resolutions where needed;</li>\n<li>Work with delivery teams to achieve success through development using CI/CD and DevOps practices, processes and tooling;</li>\n<li>Provide robust coding practices and solid unit and component test coverage, and code debugging.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>Must-have:</strong></p><ol>\n<li>\n<strong> 6+ years</strong> working experience in software development <strong>covering mobile application development</strong>, especially in Android development (Android Studio/ SDK, Java, at least one year in <strong>Kotlin</strong>).</li>\n<li>Solid experienced with architectural patterns - <strong>Clean Architecture, MVVM</strong>\n</li>\n<li>Experienced with<strong> Unit tests</strong>, UI Tests, API Testing: Mocks, Stubs;</li>\n<li>Experienced in build management tools including continuous integration and delivery practices and tools (<strong>Gradle, FastLane/Jenkins/Git</strong>);</li>\n<li>Good knowledge and experience with <strong>SOLID principles</strong>;</li>\n<li>Good understanding of modern software development practices and automation testing;</li>\n<li>Good English communication skills (both verbal &amp; written), and problem-solving and analytical skills;</li>\n</ol><p><strong>Nice-to-have:</strong></p><ol>\n<li>React Native experience;</li>\n<li>Some experience in backend technologies as well as RESTful JSON APIs, Microservices;</li>\n<li>Experienced in Performance test, Accessibility for mobile apps;</li>\n<li>Security Mobile Apps: Application Security Transport, Local Data Storage, Reverse Engineer;</li>\n<li>Experienced with device fragmentation issues.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>THE BENEFITS AND PERKS</strong></p><ol>\n<li>Very competitive remuneration package</li>\n<li>Generous private family healthcare for yourself and two family members</li>\n<li>A solid team behind you - great people who love what they do</li>\n<li>The pleasant, enthusiastic, international work environment</li>\n<li>Opportunity for traveling &amp; training in Australia</li>\n<li>A brand new &amp; state of the art Agile office</li>\n<li>Latest technologies, flexible working hours</li>\n<li>A promising training and career path</li>\n<li>Fun team activities &amp; outing</li>\n<li>English learning with native English teachers</li>\n</ol><p><strong>CLOUD FIRST</strong></p><p>NAB is undergoing an exciting \"<i>Cloud</i> First\" technology transformation by taking advantage of the latest tools and techniques used by leading technology and digital companies globally. But it’s not just about the Tech, we are also investing heavily in our people, so if you have an appetite to learn, grow and elevate others around you, this is the place for you!</p><p><strong>IT'S MORE THAN MONEY!</strong></p><p>We naturally also provide a very competitive remuneration package but a career with us is about a lot more than money. We believe in people with ideas and dreams, and we want you to achieve your aspirations. We'll work together to deliver exceptional products and outcomes that push the limits of our own aspirations. Our passion for creating value and exceeding our customers' expectations means we're constantly striving to redefine our standards of excellence. You'll have our backing to develop and our encouragement to explore, realize and reach your full potential.</p><p><strong>If this excites you, let's have a chat over a cup of coffee!</strong></p>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "nab-innovation-centre-vietnam", "job_name": "Senior/Lead Performance Tester", "tag_list": "\nTester\n\n\nQA QC\n", "location": "TNR Tower, 54A Nguyen Chi Thanh, Lang Thuong, Dong Da, Ha Noi", "three_reasons": "Very competitive remuneration package\nBuild products for millions of users in Australia\nHybrid and flexible working environment", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>We're seeking experienced and talented performance testing engineers to work on our flagship platform that serves millions of customers daily.</p><p>You will join our Agile Engineering team and manage the performance testing for the team while coaching them to have a quality mindset. You will be part of our committed Quality community, passionate about delivering a high-quality experience for our customers. To be successful, you will need to demonstrate expertise in test performance and have a solid understanding of the testing methodology.</p><p><strong>What will you be responsible for?</strong></p><ol>\n<li>Work on designing test scenarios in testing tool, workload modelling; Execute Performance Test including Load, Stress, Endurance Test, Scalability, Chaos.</li>\n<li>Develop scripts or code to simulate the business critical transactions for various protocols like HTTP/HTML, Web services using HP Performance Centre, JMeter, Gatling etc.m      </li>\n<li>Monitor server metrics using App Dynamics, CA APM, Splunk, Sitescope, Dynatrace, and investigate any bottlenecks identified during the test.</li>\n<li>Working knowledge of at least 1 programming language- Java, Scala, Python, or similar.</li>\n<li>Experience in Agile Methodologies and Agile Tools like – JIRA, Confluence, Rally, etc.</li>\n<li>Ability to use CI/CD practices and pipelines.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ol>\n<li>Good communications skills as this role will require a lot of collaborations with internal and external teams.</li>\n<li>Experience in test scripting, workload modelling, test data management, performance environment management, test design and execution, monitoring, performance bottleneck identification.</li>\n<li>Good knowledge in non-functional requirements gathering and mapping of test cases.</li>\n<li><span>Good knowledge in using performance testing tools like HP Performance Centre, JMeter, or Gatling with different protocols like HTTP/HTML, Web service, MQ, Java RMI, ODBC etc.</span></li>\n<li>Hands on experience on using build automation tools like Jenkins, Bamboo for automating performance tests and result analysis.</li>\n<li>Analyse performance test results and compare with the Non-functional requirements/SLA.</li>\n<li>Status tracking and preparing detailed test strategy, summary reports.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>THE BENEFITS AND PERKS</strong></p><ol>\n<li>Very competitive remuneration package</li>\n<li>Generous private family healthcare for yourself and your family members</li>\n<li>A solid team behind you - great people who love what they do</li>\n<li>The pleasant, enthusiastic, international work environment</li>\n<li>Opportunity for traveling &amp; training in Australia</li>\n<li>Brand new &amp; state of the art Agile offices</li>\n<li>Latest technologies, flexible working hours</li>\n<li>A promising training and career path</li>\n<li>Fun team activities &amp; outing</li>\n<li>English learning with native English teachers</li>\n</ol><p><strong>If this excites you, let's have a chat over a cup of coffee!</strong></p>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "nab-innovation-centre-vietnam", "job_name": "Senior/Middle DevOps Engineer (AWS/Azure)", "tag_list": "\nDevOps\n\n\nAWS\n", "location": "E. Town Central, 11 Doan Van Bo, District 4, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Very competitive remuneration package\nBuild products for millions of users in Australia\nHybrid and flexible working environment", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>We're seeking <strong>Senior DevOps Engineer</strong> who have had a proven track record of running critical shared application platforms in a production cloud environment who will take a team-first approach and can act as a multiplier, making other engineers better at their craft.</p><p><strong>Our Job Responsibilites</strong></p><ol>\n<li>Define/implement tools and processes to standardize and automate the way project software is developed, built, tested, and deployed; </li>\n<li>Ensure a homogeneous way of implementing continuous integration and/or continuous delivery across projects; </li>\n<li>Assist with the design and development of resilient, secure, supportable, and scalable systems; </li>\n<li>Automate infrastructure deployments and rollbacks for all developed work assuming responsibility for process support; </li>\n<li>Lead investigations into production incidents with assistance from the development team; </li>\n<li>Proactively manage any risks to the production environment; </li>\n<li>Continually improve the supportability of our systems by feeding improvements back into the design and development cycles. </li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ol>\n<li>3+ years’ extensive experience of DevOps  across all Phases of the software lifecycle</li>\n<li>Experienced in Azure or AWS cloud technologies</li>\n<li>Experience in building CI/CD pipeline automation, tooling (Github, Jenkins, Artifactory, Checkmarx, Ambassador, Splunk and Docker) and Compliance as code;</li>\n<li>Have an in-depth understanding of microservice architecture, API management, and distributed systems concepts; </li>\n<li>Experience with cloud services is essential, in particular, our core AWS Technologies (EC2, Lambda, S3, SQS, SNS, EKS, S2, RDS Oracle, Lambda, Cloudwatch, PostgreSQL &amp; Cloud Watch);</li>\n<li>AKS/EKS Kubernetes</li>\n<li>Understanding of Java and dev language/tools</li>\n<li>Experience with API gateways and technologies (e.g. REST)</li>\n<li>Other experiences: SQL, scripting, Splunk</li>\n<li>Experience hands-on Infrastructure as Code abilities e.g. Terraform, Ansible, Packer, Python.</li>\n<li>Ability to develop code and work with testers and developers</li>\n<li>Ability to lead and coach on code reviews between Developers and Quality Engineering.</li>\n<li>Experienced and highly capable in continually developing and balancing technical and soft skills with an understanding that making great software requires both problem identification and prevention</li>\n<li>Strong communication, documentation, organization, and time management skills.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>THE BENEFITS AND PERKS</strong></p><ol>\n<li>Very competitive remuneration package</li>\n<li>Generous private family healthcare for yourself and your family members</li>\n<li>A solid team behind you - great people who love what they do</li>\n<li>The pleasant, enthusiastic, international work environment</li>\n<li>Opportunity for traveling &amp; training in Australia</li>\n<li>Brand new &amp; state of the art Agile offices</li>\n<li>Latest technologies, flexible working hours</li>\n<li>A promising training and career path</li>\n<li>Fun team activities &amp; outing</li>\n<li>English learning with native English teachers</li>\n</ol><p><strong>If this excites you, let's have a chat over a cup of coffee!</strong></p>\n</div>"}
