{"company_name": "techcombank", "job_name": "Senior Officer, DevSecOps (Non – Product Team)", "tag_list": "\nDevOps\n\n\nLinux\n\n\nCloud\n", "location": "C5 Building Tower, D’Capitale Tower, 119 Tran Duy Hung, Cau Giay, Ha Noi", "three_reasons": "Top-tier banking environment in Vietnam\nChallenging opportunities for the “Greater” You\nAttractive career path and benefits", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>Job Purpose</strong></p><p>Senior Engineer, Non-Prod is responsible for providing cloud infrastructure services, system integration, automation for development units. Coordinating with development units to plan, develop, test, deploy, release, and operate service; design, deploy, automate and optimize for the operation of infrastructure services based on Cloud &amp; DevSecOps platforms</p><p><strong>Key Accountabilities (1)</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Design, Build &amp; Deliver Non-prod infrastructure on AWS cloud including components such as Network, System, Application, Databasse, Security for the development needs of projects.</li>\n<li>Build, deploy and optimize DevSecOps systems on Non-Prod environment including Tools Chain, Ways of Working, Mind Set to provide CICD pipeline for projects.</li>\n<li>Build, deploy and integrate the organization's security systems such as Monitoring, Logging, PAM, IAM, WAF, Firewall... to ensure safety and compliance</li>\n<li>Optimize resources and costs. Provide policies to effectively use resources on the Cloud such as: Resource Policy, AutoScaling Policy, Shutdown Scheduled ...</li>\n<li>Operate Midleware &amp; DB application platforms including IBM Websphere, Container (EKS/OpenShift), Database (Oracle, Postgres)</li>\n<li>Operate Cloud infrastructure including System, Network, Security, Policy; Monitor all systems, components, costs on Non-Prod . environment</li>\n<li>Provide fast infrastructure services, automate the implementation process to optimize operations, manage configurations, secure security, save time and costs.</li>\n<li>Troubleshoot, fix errors and find the root cause and solution to the problem.</li>\n<li>Resource usage reports for units to optimize resources and costs; Upgrade infrastructure services to meet security and compliance</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>Graduated from one of the fields of Computer Science/Engineering, Software Engineering or Information Technology</li>\n<li>Have at least 2 years of working experience in one of the fields of Cloud; DevOps; Linux; Web Applications such as IBM WebSphere, Apache Tomcat, Oracle WebLogic…; Databases: AWS RDS, Oracle DB, MySQL, Postgres, Caching…; and Security</li>\n<li>Directly operate systems on on-Premise, on-Cloud and Hybrid Cloud environments.</li>\n<li>Have experience in deploying infrastructure on Cloud using Infrastructure as Code tool</li>\n<li>Experience with using Configuration Manager tools in Automation jobs such as: Puppet, Ansible, Scripting</li>\n<li>Experience with implementing CICD pipeline components and components in DevSecOps Toolchains such as Containers, Git, Jenkins, Vault, Monitoring &amp; Logging solutions</li>\n<li>Have experience in Cloud transformation projects, Microservices, Automation, Integration is one of the advantages.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>WHY BECOME IT/DATA EXPERTS AT TECHCOMBANK?</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Investing <strong>over 300 million USD</strong> to develop large-scale IT projects, Techcombank is one of the leading bank in Technology trends in Vietnam</li>\n<li>You will grow with Techcombank by having the opportunity to learn from <strong>top experts</strong> from across the world</li>\n<li>Techcombank provides a <strong>rewarding remuneration structure</strong> that commensurate with your achievement and contribution</li>\n<li>Techcombank is the <strong>Top 2 Best place to work </strong>in the banking industry where you can experience various exciting activities throughout the year: Company anniversary, Team building, Active Saturday Off, Year End Party, etc.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
