{"company_name": "panasonic-vietnam-group-panasonic-r-d-center-vietnam-prdcv", "job_name": "Technical Writer (Software Documentation/Madcap)", "tag_list": "\nBusiness Analyst\n\n\nSystem Admin\n\n\nSQL\n", "location": "Lotte Tower, 54 Lieu Giai, Ba Dinh, Ha Noi", "three_reasons": "Lộ trình phát triển sự nghiệp đa chiều\nCơ hội đào tạo, công tác tại Nhật, Singapore, Mỹ..\nMức lương hấp dẫn, chế độ thưởng dựa trên năng lực", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>Duties and tasks include, but are not limited to:<br>Creating End-User Documentation<br>• Interpreting existing business documentation and functional specifications to understand the key end user information, in co-ordination with internal resources (Developers, Training, Business Analysts, etc.) as needed<br>• Considering the most effective formats for delivering content, such as general overviews, how-tos, detailed guides, and FAQs<br>• Reviewing existing resources to determine if they can be reused or if they need to be recreated<br>• Creating and/or revising content to ensure it is concise yet engaging and accessible to end users with non-technical backgrounds<br>• Proof-reading documentation to maintain a high quality standard that maintains PanaCIM’s brand voice and style guide<br>Making content available in Madcap Flare<br>• Utilizing the tools within Madcap to organize and publish content<br>• Maintaining a cohesive look and feel between articles so end users can seamlessly navigate between topics<br>• Note: in-depth training with Madcap will not be provided, so previous experience with this toolset is a significant asset<br>Providing Recommendations and Expertise<br>• Working closely with the PanaCIM Product Owner, Business Analysts, Development teams, and Training team, providing input into the design of the online knowledgebase as appropriate<br>• When possible, providing insight into industry standards and best practices for creating and maintaining documentation</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>You should be:<br>• Experienced writing technical software documentation that targets a non-technical user audience<br>• Obsessive about consistency and accuracy, with high attention to detail across all areas of work<br>• Able to thrive and produce high-quality outputs in a timely fashion with limited oversight<br>• Adaptable and able to maintain focus in a fast-paced environment where things can change quickly<br>• Open-minded and proactive, focused on resolving problems and delivering results<br>• A team player with good collaboration skills<br>• Able to seek feedback and receive constructive criticism<br>And have:<br>• A minimum of 3 years experience as a technical writer creating web-based resources<br>• Demonstrated capacity to produce excellent, clear, clean and accessible writing (samples will be requested)<br>• Strong communication skills (written and verbal)<br>• Ability to understand and communicate complex technical topics to non-technical stakeholders, both internally and externally<br>• Good proficiency with MS Office<br>• Experience with documentation publishing software</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>Panasonic R&amp;D Center Vietnam was established in April 2007, is a company specializing in R&amp;D of Panasonic Group in Vietnam with the aim of enhancing R&amp;D activities in the field of digital home appliances, automation, mobility in Vietnam, providing R&amp;D services for software solutions in today's hottest fields such as AI, Cloud, IoT in a chain of R&amp;D centers of worldwide corporations </p><p>1. Career Path Development</p><p>• Long-term multi-career roadmap;</p><p>• Learning &amp; development (Language Training, Technical Training, Soft-skill Training, On-job Training, etc.)</p><p>• Oversea business trips (Japan, China, Singapore, US, Mexico, EU, etc.)</p><p>2. Work-life Balance</p><p>• Flexible working time that supports work-life balance (Core time: 9:00-16:00; 5 days from Monday - Friday/ week)</p><p>• Additional special holiday</p><p>3. Compensation package</p><p>• Attractive salary </p><p>• Competitive bonus package depend on abilities, performance and competencies</p><p>• Diversified allowance scheme</p><p>4. Wellness</p><p>• Well-protected with 24/7 personal accident and medical care insurance;</p><p>• Well-designed Annual Health Check-up program;</p><p>5. Activities</p><p>• Team-building activities; Birthday Party; Year-end party; Sport Day/ Family Day</p><p>• Summer Vacation (Trip to famous tourist spots domestic/ overseas,…)</p>\n</div>"}
