{"company_name": "yody-fashion", "job_name": "Product Owner", "tag_list": "\nBusiness Analyst\n\n\nProduct Manager\n\n\nProject Manager\n", "location": "90 Nguyễn Tuân, Thanh Xuan, Ha Noi", "three_reasons": "YODY FASHION TECH - TẦM NHÌN LỚN\nCông ty Product (O2O, Supply Chain, ERP,...)\nCông nghệ là 1 trong 3 chiến lược quan trọng nhất", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><span>- Xây dựng sản phẩm Website và App phục vụ hàng triệu khách hàng của YODY, đưa YODY ra Global thông qua hai sản phẩm này.</span><br><span>- Chúng tôi tìm kiếm PO có năng lực phân tích cao và năng động để làm việc với đội ngũ để đưa ra định hướng tốt cho sản phẩm phục vụ khách hàng.</span><br><span>- Hiểu rõ Customer Journey để tối ưu trải nghiệm trên từng điểm chạm.</span><br><span>- Quản lý Product Backlog hiệu quả.</span><br><span>- Hiện thực hóa các yêu cầu Product Requirement đưa ra các user story cụ thể.</span><br><span>- Thu thập dữ liệu từ  khách hàng thông qua sự kết hợp của các đánh giá quan sát, lập bản đồ quy trình, phỏng vấn các bên liên quan và các nguồn dữ liệu theo ngữ cảnh.</span><br><span>- Làm đầu mối giao tiếp kết nối giữa các thành viên trong dự án (Dev, UI, UX, R&amp;D, PM..v.v...) bao gồm chuyển thông tin và cùng thảo luận về yêu cầu khách hàng, về dự án.</span><br><span>- Thu thập thông tin khảo sát, đánh giá từ khách hàng và nội bộ; phân tích phối hợp với team dự án đưa ra giải pháp.</span><br><span>- Làm việc với Dev team để phát triển các yêu cầu đúng cam kết.</span><br><span>- Tham gia nghiệm thu sản phẩm trước khi thực hiện chuyển giao.</span><br><span>- Thời gian làm việc: 8h-17h, nghỉ các Chủ nhật</span></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><span>- Nam/Nữ: 25 - 35 tuổi.</span><br><span>- Ứng viên tốt nghiệp Đại học chuyên ngành Công nghệ thông tin, Kinh tế, tài chính, thương mại, hoặc có kinh nghiệm thực tiễn ở các ngành liên quan.</span><br><span>- Đã từng phát triển các hệ thống website/app có triệu người dùng.</span><br><span>- Có kinh nghiệm 2 năm ở vị trí tương đương PO.</span><br><span>- Có kinh nghiệm trong mảng bán lẻ là một lợi thế.</span><br><span>- Ưu tiên ứng viên có kinh nghiệm thực tiễn về quy trình phát triển phần mềm Scrum/Agile.</span><br><span>- Biết cách thiết kế tài liệu cho người dùng cuối/khách hàng nội bộ.</span><br><span>- Biết vẽ UML Diagram (Sequence diagram, use case diagram,...)</span><br><span>- Có các chứng chỉ về BABOK là một lợi thế.</span></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><span>+ Thu nhập 25 - 60tr/tháng</span><br><span>+ Thưởng cuối năm: 1 - 3 tháng thu nhập, thưởng theo doanh thu, thưởng các ngày Lễ, Tết</span><br><span>- Công ty là trường học: Công ty chi trả 100% các khóa học nội bộ/ bên ngoài</span><br><span>- Văn hóa doanh nghiệp khác biệt: Văn hóa phục vụ, môi trường trẻ trung, năng động, nhiều cơ hội thăng tiến</span><br><span>- Và các chính sách, phúc lợi khác:</span><br><span>+ Nghỉ chủ nhật, năm có 12 ngày nghỉ phép</span><br><span>+ Đóng bảo hiểm khi chính thức theo quy định</span><br><span>+ Phụ cấp Ăn trưa miễn phí tại công ty.</span><br><span>+ Được tổ chức sinh nhật, du lịch 1-2 lần/năm, hưởng các chính sách đãi ngộ đặc biệt từ công ty</span></p>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "hrs-group", "job_name": "Mid/Senior DevOps Engineer (AWS)", "tag_list": "\nDevOps\n\n\nEnglish\n\n\nAWS\n", "location": "Anna building, Quang Trung sofware city, District 12, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Attractive salary package and valuable benefits\nGet the opportunity to access global L&D programs\nInternational and innovative working environment", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>In the responsible position of the <strong>DevOps Engineer, </strong>the future position holder is responsible to build the next generation of APIs and Services. As a <strong>DevOps Engineer,</strong> you are responsible for the development and, mainly, maintenance of our backend components to ensure stabilization and enable our exclusive services for our customers.</p><ul>\n<li>Be part of a team to develop and deploy the Backend applications on AWS cloud architecture using Java and relevant technologies.</li>\n<li>Define and manage cloud infrastructure as code (IAC), improve CI/CD pipeline, ensure scalability and availability of the system, build a monitoring stack, and automate build, configuration, and deployment orchestration scripts</li>\n<li>Utilize a broad toolset for DevOps/Infra and leverage variety of services from AWS</li>\n<li>Improve speed, efficiency, and scalability of all systems.</li>\n<li>Build and optimize CI and CD for operation and deployment as automatically as possible.</li>\n<li>Monitor, troubleshoot and manage all environments of the team.</li>\n<li>Work with the engineering team and take architectural decisions.</li>\n<li>Have knowledge of network protocols and standards.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor’s Degree in IT technology or related field</li>\n<li>Understanding and experience with AWS.</li>\n<li>Practical experience with multiple Infrastructures as Code, Containerized Orchestration like Docker, Kubernetes</li>\n<li>Extensive experience setting up and maintaining CI/CD processes like GitHub Actions.</li>\n<li>Experience and understand the concept of software architecture and its related technologies: Monolithic, Microservice, RESTfull API/ SOAP, CDN, etc.…</li>\n<li>Understanding and experience with networking (TCP, UDP ...)</li>\n<li>Experience with source control and related concepts</li>\n<li>Proactive and self-driven</li>\n<li>Fluency in English, spoken and written.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>Attractive salary - performance bonus and valuable benefits </li>\n<li>International and innovative working environment with Germany, Australia, Poland, Ukraine, etc. </li>\n<li>Challenging projects with onsite opportunities in Europe </li>\n<li>Supportive working conditions: Laptop, MS Surface Hub, pure pantry with coffee, soft drink, snacks, etc. </li>\n<li>Premium company traveling program and other exciting activities. </li>\n<li>Highly appreciate your idea and constantly supporting your skill development. </li>\n<li>Premium healthcare for employees.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "hrs-group", "job_name": "Automation QA/Software Tester (Selenium, Java)", "tag_list": "\nTester\n\n\nJava\n\n\nQA QC\n", "location": "Anna building, Quang Trung sofware city, District 12, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Attractive salary package and valuable benefits\nGet the opportunity to access global L&D programs\nInternational and innovative working environment", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>We are looking for a passionate QA Automation Engineer to ensure quality and excellence in our software, test deliverables, and automation plans and enable our continued growth.</p><p><strong>CHALLENGE</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Work with the product &amp; development teams on requirement specifications.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with development teams (Backend &amp; Web) on Quality Testing(integration, end-to-end, etc.). Configure automated tests to execute reliably and efficiently in CI/CD environments.</li>\n<li>Work with engineers and product managers to implement testing into the software development process at an early stage.</li>\n<li>Analyze test results and document and report defects.</li>\n<li>Proactively write test automation for new features and existing use cases. Develop and maintain test documentation.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>2+ years of work experience in testing web- and app-based software solutions and Quality Assurance.</li>\n<li>Strong knowledge of software QA methodologies, tools, and processes.</li>\n<li>Proven track record of working with product management, developers, and production engineering in an Agile environment.</li>\n<li>Experience in web services automated testing (REST API).</li>\n<li>Fluency in programming languages (Python, Java, etc.) to automate manual testing or tasks.</li>\n<li>Knowledge of CI/CD tools is a big advantage.</li>\n<li>Hands-on experience with QA from start to end of the software development lifecycle.</li>\n<li>Very good organization, communication, and interpersonal skills (including Team management/collaboration skills).</li>\n<li>Can communicate in English.</li>\n<li>Strong analytical &amp; problem-solving skills.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>PERSPECTIVE</strong></p><p>Access to a global network of a globally united and mutually responsible “Tribe of Intrapreneurs” that is passionately dedicated to renew the travel industry and while doing so reinvent the ways how businesses stay, work and pay.<br><br>Our entrepreneurial driven environment of full ownership and execution focus offers you the playground to contribute to a greater mission, while growing personally and professionally throughout this unique journey. You will continuously learn from a radical culture of retrospectives and continuous improvement and actively contribute to making business life better, smarter and more sustainable.</p><p><strong>BENEFITS</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Your voice is listened and your skill development is supported constantly.</li>\n<li>Working with colleagues and experts at other offices such as Germany, Australia, Poland, Ukraine....</li>\n<li>Salary is very attractive and competitive.</li>\n<li>Rewarding outstanding contributions by the project bonus, quarterly bonus and yearly bonus.</li>\n<li>Supportive working conditions: laptop, nice office, pure pantry with coffee, soft drink, snacks.....</li>\n<li>Fully compliance with Vietnam Labor Code, especially the insurance is based on full salary.</li>\n<li>Additional standard benefits: additional health insurance, company trip and business travel, training, year-end party, team outing activities..</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "diag", "job_name": "Senior PHP Developer", "tag_list": "\nPHP\n\n\nLaravel\n", "location": "414-416-418-420 Cao Thang Street, Ward 12, District 10, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Competitive compensation.\nYoung and International environment\nFlexibility to work from home", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>Are you a Software Engineer with extensive programming experience? Is your code fast, efficient and reliable? Do you particularly enjoy working with amazing people, having fun at work and building something awesome? If so, let's talk!</p><p>We're not looking for stack experts. We're looking for smart people who can bring in the best tools and processes to get the job done.</p><p>As Senior PHP Software Engineer, this position involves:</p><p>● Product development in <strong>PHP/Laravel.</strong></p><p>● <strong>Integrations</strong> between our product to 3rd party APIs.</p><p>● Work in an <strong>Agile environment</strong> with strong attention to a well-documented code, unit testing, and continuous integration.</p><p>● Being able to <strong>mentor, coach, and train other colleagues</strong>.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>Required skills and experience:</strong></p><p>● At least 3 years of experience coding in PHP language</p><p>● \"Product Engineering\" mindset.</p><p>● Pragmatism and obsession for simplicity, efficiency, and performance.</p><p>● An expert level at <strong>server-side</strong>, <strong>client-side</strong> or <strong>full stack development</strong>. Your final role within the team will depend on your skills and internal training will be provided.</p><p>● Obsession for <strong>quality</strong> and <strong>testing</strong>.</p><p>● Eager to <strong>learn new technologies</strong> and frameworks.</p><p>● Strong <strong>communication skills</strong>.</p><p>● <strong>English</strong> is required. Part of our team only speaks English (And the screening is done by our English speaker Head of Engineering)</p><p><strong>Bonus points for:</strong></p><p>● Experience with <strong>Python and/or Vue.js.</strong> or other general purpose language.</p><p>● DevOps experience with the <strong>GCP</strong> suite.</p><p>● Experience with Event-Oriented Architecture. We have a cool Apache Kafka.</p><p>● Experience working with high-performing, Agile development teams.</p><p>● Want to learn about the HealthCare industry and have an impact on how doctors can diagnose their patients.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>Competitive compensation.</li>\n<li>Flexibility to work from home.</li>\n<li>Health perks.</li>\n<li>Meal allowance.</li>\n<li>Young and International environment.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "diag", "job_name": "Senior FrontEnd Developer (VueJS, Typescript)", "tag_list": "\nVueJS\n\n\nJavaScript\n\n\nTypeScript\n", "location": "414-416-418-420 Cao Thang Street, Ward 12, District 10, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Competitive compensation.\nYoung and International environment\nFlexibility to work from home", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>Are you a Software Engineer with extensive programming experience? Is your code fast, efficient and reliable? Do you particularly enjoy working with amazing people, having fun at work and building something awesome? If so, let's talk!</p><p>We're not looking for stack experts. We're looking for smart people who can bring in the best tools and processes to get the job done.</p><p><strong>As FrontEnd Developer, this position involves:</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Define and shape the fundamentals of engineering at Diag.</li>\n<li>Design and write maintainable code at scale</li>\n<li>Discuss/propose solution to improve User Experience</li>\n<li>Continuously discuss, debate with other team members to propose optimal solutions for different problems</li>\n</ul><p><strong>Daily tasks:</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Build and deploy performant modern web applications in Vue.js</li>\n<li>Convert from design/prototype to responsive interface on the web</li>\n<li>Work with product managers, data analysts and UI designers to implement products and features, and test their impact to business metrics.</li>\n<li>Participate in code and design reviews to maintain our high development standards</li>\n<li>Engage in service capacity and demand planning, software performance analysis, tuning and optimization</li>\n<li>Collaborate with product and experience teams to define and prototype feature specifications</li>\n<li>Design, build, analyze and fix large-scale systems</li>\n<li>Learn full-stack performance tuning and optimization</li>\n<li>Debug and modify complex, production software</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>Required skills and experience:</strong></p><ul>\n<li>At least 5 years of experience coding.</li>\n<li>Product Engineering\" mindset.</li>\n<li>Basic understanding of User Experience.</li>\n<li>Strong understanding of <strong>Vuejs, Typecript.</strong>\n</li>\n<li>Pragmatism and obsession for simplicity, efficiency, and performance.</li>\n<li>Obsession for <strong>quality</strong> and <strong>testing</strong>.</li>\n<li>Strong <strong>communication skills</strong>.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>English</strong> is required. Part of our team only speaks English (And the screening is done by our English speaker Head of Engineering)</li>\n</ul><p><strong>Bonus points for:</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Experience working with high-performing, Agile development teams.</li>\n<li>Want to learn about the HealthCare industry and have an impact on how doctors can diagnose their patients.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>100% salary in probation time.</li>\n<li>Full social insurance starting from probation time.</li>\n<li>Hybrid working mode.</li>\n<li>Laptop, monitor provided.</li>\n<li>Health perks.</li>\n<li>Meal allowance.</li>\n<li>Young and International environment.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "diag", "job_name": "Data Lead", "tag_list": "\nDatabase\n\n\nPython\n\n\nSQL\n", "location": "414-416-418-420 Cao Thang Street, Ward 12, District 10, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Competitive compensation.\nYoung and International environment\nFlexibility to work from home", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>At the Diag Company, we are looking for your talent to strengthen and grow our community of apps and platforms experts. Joining us is joining a company that resembles you, building itself as you express your talents, your passion, and communicate your ideas.</p><p>To be perfectly sure, here is all the information you need!!</p><p><strong>About the team:</strong></p><p>The Data Team is Responsible for data analysis of operation strategy including sales team Strategy, Doctor adoption Strategy, Business performance, and reporting</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Responsible for data analysis of operation strategy including Sales Team Strategy, Doctor Adoption Strategy, Business performance, and reporting;</li>\n<li>Lead the data analysis for our Vietnamese market going forward, able to coach and grow the team;</li>\n<li>Design the monitoring systems independently to reflect any changes of business in time;</li>\n<li>Cooperate with the Ops team to set strategy, e.g. finding potential doctors and clinics, measuring LTV of clients, figuring out the growth strategy of merchants, etc.;</li>\n<li>Follow up the data analysis of business teams, support the operation effect and give the follow-up optimization suggestions;</li>\n<li>Describe the situation of business, explain the fluctuations of business and provide valuable suggestions with reports;</li>\n<li>Cooperate with PM / Ops team / R&amp;D, promote the implementation of optimization scheme, and bring about the actual improvement and growth of the business;</li>\n<li>Cooperate with R&amp;D and Data PM to build data systems and user-friendly data products to support business.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>Master degree or above, major in mathematics, statistics, computer science is preferred; or major in science or engineering or engaged in data statistics, analysis, modeling related working areas after graduation;</li>\n<li>At least 7 years of working experience in data science track, and have a good business sense in e-commerce;</li>\n<li>At least 2 years of people management experience required;</li>\n<li>Proficient in SQL/Hive/Python or R, experienced in massive data manipulation, machine learning &amp; modeling;</li>\n<li>Solid technical &amp; knowledge of A/B testing methodologies, can consistently explore and find the best practice</li>\n<li>Insightful data sense and rigorous logical mindset, capable of providing systematic approaches to solve business problems;</li>\n<li>Global working experience or analytical experience is preferred;</li>\n<li>Written and verbal English skills are required for daily communications with global teams;</li>\n<li>Have a strong learning ability and curiosity; Quickly familiar with and starting a new business; Can lead a small project team to support business;</li>\n<li>Have a strong ability to work under pressure, have the courage to overcome difficulties, and accept challenges.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>Competitive compensation.</li>\n<li>Flexibility to work from home.</li>\n<li>Health perks.</li>\n<li>Meal allowance.</li>\n<li>Young and International environment.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "onpoint", "job_name": "Technical Manager (Golang, Python, Ruby)", "tag_list": "\nGolang\n\n\nPython\n\n\nRuby\n", "location": " Floor 4, AB Building, 27B Nguyen Dinh Chieu,, District 1, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Opportunity for regional scale (South East Asia)\nEnrich your skills and develop your potential\nEnjoy motivating working conditions", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>Onpoint is the largest E-commerce enabler in Vietnam, providing end-to-end services, helping brands to accelerate and become more successful online in Vietnam and SEA region. Onpoint's mission is to make E-commerce easy for brands, to create sustainable values for businesses, consumers, and partners.</p><p>It's a privilege for us to serve top tier clients. Our integrated capabilities encompass all aspects of the E-commerce value chain covering store commercial and operations, digital marketing, customer services, warehousing, and fulfillment. We help a brand execute their E-com strategies by selling their goods directly to customers online or by providing services to assist with their E-com operations. Our business ranges from the largest online shopping platforms as well as social shopping channels.</p><p>Since day one, we have dedicated ourselves to the needs of our brand partners. We work closely to ensure our direction and thought processes are tightly aligned with their needs</p><p>Join us, make a difference, and create value for life!</p><p>Reporting to the <strong>CTO</strong> you will be responsible for:</p><ul>\n<li>Implement and evolve patterns, practices, and processes to support effective design, development, and delivery of customer value, in partnership with engineering leaders, and Product Leaders.</li>\n<li>Coach and mentor engineering leaders, individual engineers to be more effective individual contributors.</li>\n<li>Ensure adherence to established patterns, practices, and processes in areas of immediate responsibility and across engineering.</li>\n<li>Architect the system and review code for highly scalable SAAS.</li>\n<li>Should be strong in building the high-quality system in either Elixir/Golang/Python or any functional languages.</li>\n<li>Involving in strategic and operational decision making.</li>\n<li>Understand and convey the product vision to the team and drive initiatives to achieve them.</li>\n<li>Responsible mentoring, development, and managing an entire team of engineers to grow a high-performance engineering organization.</li>\n<li>Ensuring technology teams deliver major initiatives that drive our service/system growth.</li>\n<li>Participate in product team iteration planning, release planning, and coordination of dependencies.</li>\n<li>Work closely with Product, Business, Quality Control teams to understand and track to closure product implementation, enhancements, and changes.</li>\n<li>Management of roadmap milestone deliveries.</li>\n<li>Create, communicate, and ensure compliance of high coding standards.</li>\n<li>Drive DevOps to ensure appropriate monitoring, alerting, incident management, and problem resolution for products and services.</li>\n<li>Understand Users &amp; Drive conversions by employing analytics &amp; User behavior.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>Must have: </strong></p><ul>\n<li>Bachelor’s degree in computer science, information systems or a related field.</li>\n<li>Record of accomplishment of successful management of Infrastructure, Site Reliability and Platforms.</li>\n<li>Experience leading and growing a high performing engineering organization.</li>\n<li>Demonstrated effectiveness as a coach and mentor to engineering leaders and individual engineers.</li>\n<li>Record of accomplishment of recruiting, retaining, and growing high performing talent.</li>\n<li>Experience with architectural patterns of large, high-scale applications.</li>\n<li>Shipped several large-scale projects with multiple dependencies across teams.</li>\n<li>Must have hands-on experience in Elixir/Go/Python, Aws, Microservices.</li>\n</ul><p><strong>Nice to have: </strong></p><ul>\n<li>Experience with Redis, Elasticsearch has knowledge of Caching is a plus.</li>\n<li>Experience with PostgreSQL others (MySQL, NoSQL, etc.) is a plus.</li>\n<li>Good knowledge of eCommerce, Saas, etc.</li>\n<li>Knowledge of Integrations with various Third-party CRMs.</li>\n<li>Effective communication, planning, critical thinking, and organizational skills required. Must be able to understand users, analyze data, solve problems, make decisions, and continuously improve.</li>\n<li>Ability to work under pressure with time constraints.</li>\n<li>Experience with agile development processes and frequent release cycles.</li>\n<li>Great interest in eCommerce.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>An opportunity to learn at a company that is growing on a regional scale (South East Asia)</li>\n<li>Working in a young, super-talented, and supportive team environment</li>\n<li>Company trip, team building</li>\n<li>PTI Insurance, Full package Insurance</li>\n<li>MacBook for Developer</li>\n<li>Bonus project</li>\n<li>Bonus KPI/Month</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "onpoint", "job_name": "Product Owner (Business Analyst, Product Manager)", "tag_list": "\nProduct Manager\n\n\nEnglish\n\n\nBusiness Analyst\n", "location": " Floor 4, AB Building, 27B Nguyen Dinh Chieu,, District 1, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Opportunity for regional scale (South East Asia)\nEnrich your skills and develop your potential\nEnjoy motivating working conditions", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><span>OnPoint is the largest E-commerce enabler in Vietnam, providing end-to-end services, helping brands to accelerate and become more successful online in Vietnam and SEA region. OnPoint's mission is to make E-commerce easy for brands, to create sustainable values for businesses, consumers, and partners.</span></p><p><span>It's a privilege for us to serve top-tier clients. Our integrated capabilities encompass all aspects of the E-commerce value chain covering store commercial and operations, digital marketing, customer services, warehousing, and fulfillment. We help a brand execute their E-com strategies by selling their goods directly to customers online or by providing services to assist with their E-com operations. Our business ranges from the largest online shopping platforms as well as social shopping channels.</span></p><p><span>Since day one, we have dedicated ourselves to the needs of our brand partners. We work closely to ensure our direction and thought processes are tightly aligned with their needs</span></p><p><span>Join us, make a difference, and create value for life!</span></p><p><span><strong>Reporting to the </strong></span><span><strong>Product Manager </strong></span><span><strong>you will be responsible for:</strong></span></p><ul>\n<li><span>Think ahead about business requirements and take a leadership role in the product roadmap from customer experiences/requirements/ functionality perspectives of the technology platform, considering the business context</span></li>\n<li><span>Present your recommendations to the CTO and Product Manager on a regular basis.</span></li>\n<li><span>Design application by coming up with &amp; analyzing requirements; studying system capabilities; understanding about product &amp; business; writing specifications.</span></li>\n<li><span>Planning what to be built that improves company productivity, increases revenue or reduces cost on feature base.</span></li>\n<li><span>Collaborate closely with relevant teams and Designer to propose appropriate solutions, present and explain specifications and requirements</span></li>\n<li><span>Document business and system requirements clearly, comprehensively, and make sure everyone can easily understand.</span></li>\n<li><span>Follow development progress, support clarify the requirement to the development team and facilities to help deliver products successfully.</span></li>\n<li><span>Discuss, develop, and review test plans and test cases required for feature/functionality with the development team to ensure development is aligned with features defined.</span></li>\n<li><span>Work with graphics to create wireframes and design the look &amp; feel of the product.</span></li>\n<li><span>Be flexible in a start-up to take on other business activities as we scale up and disrupt an eCommerce industry.</span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li><span>Having 2+ years of professional experience as a Product Owner, Product Manager or Business Analyst</span></li>\n<li><span>Having a product mindset &amp; a strong passion for building products</span></li>\n<li><span>Strong experience in writing functional specifications, describing UX, designing wireframes, explaining business rules</span></li>\n<li><span>Good Communication, good English skills</span></li>\n<li><span>Attention to details</span></li>\n<li><span>Analytical and structured work method &amp; Logical thinking</span></li>\n<li><span>IT background is a plus</span></li>\n<li><span>Project management skills</span></li>\n<li><span>Having experience in digital marketing and/or growth hacking</span></li>\n<li><span>Experience with agile development processes and frequent release cycles.</span></li>\n<li><span>Great interest in Ecommerce</span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>Hone your creativity, invent and innovate, and set your own highest standards within a nurturing, equal opportunity environment. With our tremendous growth, we seek dynamic, entrepreneurial and broad-minded individuals to join us.</p><p> </p>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "hrs-group", "job_name": "[Middle/Senior] Java Backend Engineer (AWS)", "tag_list": "\nJava\n\n\nEnglish\n\n\nAWS\n", "location": "Anna building, Quang Trung sofware city, District 12, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Attractive salary package and valuable benefits\nGet the opportunity to access global L&D programs\nInternational and innovative working environment", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>We are looking for a Senior Java Backend Developer (m/f/d) that will contribute to the national &amp; international development teams to build new products as well as implement third-party software components into the HRS Software Landscape. These new products will help our customers to manage their work-life smart, safe, and in a fully sustainable way – from arranging convenient overnight stays to booking flexible workplaces and making payments on the go, the intelligent mobile companion comprises all essentials needed to make travel hassle-free, rewarding and above all CO2 neutral. </p><p><strong>CHALLENGE</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Create solutions for our biggest clients like Amazon, Google, and Siemens</li>\n<li>Collaborate across teams with regard to overarching technical concepts and practices</li>\n<li>Work closely with our Product Owners, Product Head, Team members, and DevOps to ensure continuously<br>delivery of high-quality solutions to our clients</li>\n<li>Promote high quality aimed at areas such as security, reliability, testability, and maintainability</li>\n<li>Drive innovation by contributing new ideas for our processes, tools, and technologies </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>FOR THIS EXCITING MISSION YOU ARE EQUIPPED WITH...</strong></p><ul>\n<li>3+ years of proven hands-on Java Software Development experience </li>\n<li>Strong knowledge of modern software engineering principles, patterns, and best practices. Understanding of micro-service and serverless architectures.</li>\n<li>Experience designing and developing Restful APIs</li>\n<li>Experience with cloud-native data stores and data processing systems</li>\n<li>Experience in developing/deploying solutions to AWS Cloud</li>\n<li>Experience with relational and non-relational data stores</li>\n<li>Exposure to fault-tolerant, highly available distributed systems</li>\n<li>Ability to work in a team, fast learning, and enthusiasm for the realization of innovative products</li>\n<li>Can communicate in English</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>OUR BENEFIT</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Competitive salary - performance bonus and valuable benefits.</li>\n<li>Challenging projects with onsite opportunities in Europe.</li>\n<li>Supportive working conditions: Laptop, MS Surface Hub, pure pantry with coffee, soft drink, snacks, etc.</li>\n<li>Premium company traveling program and other exciting activities.</li>\n<li>Highly appreciate your idea and constantly supporting your skill development.</li>\n<li>International and innovative working environment with Germany, Australia, Poland, Ukraine, etc.</li>\n<li>Premium healthcare for employees.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "simple-tech-investment", "job_name": "Senior Product Manager (Business Analyst) Upto$2500", "tag_list": "\nProduct Manager\n\n\nProject Manager\n\n\nBusiness Analyst\n", "location": "402 Nguyễn Thị Minh Khai, District 3, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Competitive packages Parking fee & Lunch allowance\nFlexible working hour. Annual leave 15 days/ year\nRoom to grow professionally. Sponsorship for L&D", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>In this role, you are expected to take accountability for products in the B2C (or B2B) group that continuously contribute to the business goals of the company including</p><ul>\n<li>Lead and further develop vision, mission, and strategies with KPIs for all products/modules in your group</li>\n<li>Observe the Vietnam market, identify, initially validate relevant opportunities and support your team validating in a systematic, pragmatic way with clear measurable goals</li>\n<li>Coordinate the different activities related to the Discovery, Delivery, Go to Market, Operations of our product portfolio, by leveraging and supporting the different teams in Marketing, Business Development, Product Design, User Research, Monetization, Data and Engineering</li>\n<li>Lead, inspire, and further develop a team of Product Managers in the B2C (or B2B) group.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Experience </strong>in<strong> </strong>Software / Digital Product Management,<strong> ideally shipping multi-products/ </strong>modules in<strong> B2C </strong>(with a huge number of users)<strong> </strong>OR<strong> </strong>modules in<strong> B2B </strong>(SaaS or relevant experience like Operational Excellence)</li>\n<li>Experience in managing a team of highly independent professionals. You're somebody who inspires your team and is able to manage by influence and coaching.</li>\n<li>Excellent internal stakeholder management, synthesis, and communication skills. Ability to conceptualize and structure complex ideas and turn them into clear and actionable plans/decision frameworks/processes to support your team</li>\n<li>Tracked records of delivering successful features/products that achieve key business outcomes</li>\n<li>Results-oriented, strong ownership of your work, and will do everything as needed to get the work done</li>\n<li>Good problem-solving skills, well-structured written and verbal communication</li>\n<li>Good English (Reading, Listening is enough)</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>100% salary on your</strong> <strong>probation period.</strong>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>15 full-paid </strong>days off per year<strong>.</strong>\n</li>\n<li>13th-month <strong>bonus salary.</strong>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Room to grow with support from the team and sponsorship for L&amp;D.</strong></li>\n<li>\n<i><strong>Performance</strong></i> review 2 times/year.</li>\n<li>Competitive packages.</li>\n<li>Room to grow professionally, sponsorship for learning &amp; development of related skills.</li>\n<li>Opportunity to work on a mission that can transform the lives of millions of Vietnamese.</li>\n<li>Annual Performance Bonuses (up to 2 salary months per year).</li>\n<li>Parking fee &amp; Lunch allowance.</li>\n<li>Annual Health Checkup, Premium Health Care (Manager level), Accident Insurance for all members.</li>\n<li>Enjoy a variety of corporate events, from sports competitions, monthly birthday parties, and team building to Year-End Party, etc.</li>\n<li>Flat, open, and fast-paced environment where every idea is welcomed.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "secutix", "job_name": "Senior Java Developer - 24Hr Quick Recruitment Campaign", "tag_list": "\nJava\n\n\nSQL\n\n\nSpring\n", "location": "Melody 2 Tower – N1, Dien Bien Phu, Binh Thanh, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Product environment, startup mindset\nOpen, dynamic, international working environment\nGreat package, 18 leave days, travel to Europe", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><i><strong> 24Hr Quick Recruitment Campaign</strong> will be applied from February to April 2023</i></p><p>** Your mission **</p><ul>\n<li>You will be part of a team of skilled software engineers to develop mission-critical distributed applications for a broad range of clients and industries, using state-of-the-art tools and agile methodologies.</li>\n<li>Work closely with business analysts and software architects to design reliable, secure, and highly efficient systems; participate directly in technical decisions.</li>\n<li>Program new features and correct software defects.</li>\n<li>Be actively involved in the complete project lifecycle, from requirements analysis to final delivery.</li>\n<li>Contribute to knowledge sharing and continuous improvement activities.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science.</li>\n<li>4-8 years of experience in software analysis, design and development in JAVA.</li>\n<li>Expertise in most of the following: Spring Framework, Hibernate, Junit, SQL, database design.</li>\n<li>Very strong technical, analytical and problem solving skills.</li>\n<li>Strong sense of ownership and responsibility for code quality that follows best practices.</li>\n<li>Strong interpersonal skills, flexibility and a strong team spirit.</li>\n<li>Some experience in leading a project or team will be a plus.</li>\n<li>Experience in these technologies and tools would be a plus: Angular, KendoUI, Java FX, GWT, gRPC, Spring Boot, Fitnesse, GIT, Jenkins, Sonar, SQL Server, Oracle database, etc.</li>\n<li>Good skills in English (required).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>Perks you will love</strong>:</p><ul>\n<li>Product for 150+ customers, <strong>millions of users worldwide</strong>\n</li>\n<li>Exposure to world famous customer organizations</li>\n<li>Swiss grade work organization &amp; quality</li>\n<li>Frequent interactions with Switzerland/France/UK/Spain</li>\n<li>Build a <strong>fast &amp; solid career path</strong> with clear &amp; attractive promotion opportunities</li>\n<li>Advanced software factory &amp; technical environments</li>\n<li>300+ machines in build pipeline, 60+ technologies</li>\n<li>300+ deliveries per year, full automated test suite</li>\n</ul><p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Premium Health Insurance Package</li>\n<li>Fun, regular team building activities</li>\n<li>Love from the team. We are very <strong>collaborative &amp; friendly</strong>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Travel opportunities</strong> <strong>to</strong> visit our customers in <strong>Europe</strong>\n</li>\n<li>English class, training, strong support for career development</li>\n<li>Paralleled coaching &amp; training from <strong>industry-leading experts</strong>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "simple-tech-investment", "job_name": "Senior Data Engineer (SQL, ETL, Python) Upto$1800", "tag_list": "\nDatabase\n\n\nPython\n\n\nNoSQL\n", "location": "402 Nguyễn Thị Minh Khai, District 3, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Competitive packages Parking fee & Lunch allowance\nFlexible working hour. Annual leave 15 days/ year\nRoom to grow professionally. Sponsorship for L&D", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>Possess an understanding of the data structures and governance.</li>\n<li>Build the infrastructure required for optimal extraction, transformation, and loading of data from a wide variety of data sources.</li>\n<li>Design and maintain optimal data and machine learning pipeline architecture.</li>\n<li>Assemble large, complex data sets to build data mart that meet functional/non-functional business requirements.</li>\n<li>Communicate effectively with Developers and Business users to understand and clarify requirements.</li>\n<li>Support internal training and proper documentation ensuring the successful onboarding of new team members</li>\n<li>Implement internal process improvements: automating manual processes, optimizing data delivery, re-designing infrastructure for greater scalability, etc.</li>\n<li>Develop efficient software code for multiple use cases leveraging Spark and Big Data Technologies for various use cases built on the platform.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor’s degree in computer science, engineering, mathematics, or a related technical discipline.</li>\n<li>3+ years’ experience working as a Data Engineer role, ETL with large amounts of data.</li>\n<li>Experience with data warehousing architecture and data modeling, ETL data pipeline.</li>\n<li>Experience with using the following software/tool in the big data field.</li>\n<li>Big data tools: Apache Spark, Presto, Kafka,...</li>\n<li>NoSQL and OLAP database: MongoDB, Elastic search, etc.</li>\n<li>Data pipeline and workflow management tools: <strong>Airflow</strong>.</li>\n<li>Good at programming languages: Scala, <strong>Python</strong>, <strong>Java</strong>.</li>\n<li>Experience with SRE, Patching &amp; Automation: <strong>Kubernetes</strong> or Docker &amp; Containerization</li>\n<li>Experience in the data testing process.</li>\n<li>Experience in performing root cause analysis, identify problems and propose recommendations for improvement.</li>\n<li>Strong organizational and multitasking skills with the ability to balance competing priorities</li>\n<li>Fundamental knowledge of modern cloud computing platforms and concepts is a plus (AWS/<strong>GCP</strong>)</li>\n</ul><p>Who we are looking for</p><p>“Attitude is more important than aptitude”: we greatly value people who possess the 3 personal traits:</p><ul>\n<li>Growth mindset</li>\n<li>Curiosity</li>\n<li>Automation</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>100% salary on your</strong> <strong>probation period.</strong>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>15 full-paid </strong>days off per year<strong>.</strong>\n</li>\n<li>13th-month <strong>bonus salary.</strong>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Room to grow with support from the team and sponsorship for L&amp;D.</strong></li>\n<li>\n<i><strong>Performance</strong></i> review 2 times/year.</li>\n<li>Competitive packages.</li>\n<li>Room to grow professionally, sponsorship for learning &amp; development of related skills.</li>\n<li>Opportunity to work on a mission that can transform the lives of millions of Vietnamese.</li>\n<li>Annual Performance Bonuses (up to 2 salary months per year).</li>\n<li>Parking fee &amp; Lunch allowance.</li>\n<li>Annual Health Checkup, Premium Health Care (Manager level), Accident Insurance for all members.</li>\n<li>Enjoy a variety of corporate events, from sports competitions, monthly birthday parties, and team building to Year-End Party, etc.</li>\n<li>Flat, open, and fast-paced environment where every idea is welcomed.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "simple-tech-investment", "job_name": "Senior Data Analyst (SQL, Database, BI tools) Upto$1700", "tag_list": "\nData Analyst\n\n\nDatabase\n\n\nSQL\n", "location": "402 Nguyễn Thị Minh Khai, District 3, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Competitive packages Parking fee & Lunch allowance\nFlexible working hour. Annual leave 15 days/ year\nRoom to grow professionally. Sponsorship for L&D", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>Own the entire data flow from business objectives → transactional databases → analytical data warehouse → dashboards → insights and machine learning models</li>\n<li>Gather requirements, create detailed plans, and conduct data analysis projects</li>\n<li>Proactively follow partner's operations, and guide their action plans based on insights</li>\n<li>Conceptualize, develop, and maintain dashboards and visualizations</li>\n<li>Evaluate and define product and business metrics</li>\n<li>Design, run and analyze trial experiments in both business and product domains</li>\n<li>Partner with data warehouse team and data scientists to build high-quality data sets and machine learning models.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>Have strong experience in SQL, data analysis, and data visualization skills using BI tools (Datastudio, GoogleSheets, etc.)</li>\n<li>Experienced with statistical analyses</li>\n<li>From 3+ years’ experience in similar roles, experience in tech companies would be advantageous.</li>\n<li>Excellent communication skills, and ability to work with business and technical stakeholders.</li>\n<li>Proactive problem solving, have an eye for detail.</li>\n<li>Understanding of supply-demand theory, platform growth hacking, and product development.</li>\n<li>Proficient with R would be a plus</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>100% salary on your</strong> <strong>probation period.</strong>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>15 full-paid </strong>days off per year<strong>.</strong>\n</li>\n<li>13th-month <strong>bonus salary.</strong>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Room to grow with support from the team and sponsorship for L&amp;D.</strong></li>\n<li>\n<i><strong>Performance</strong></i> review 2 times/year.</li>\n<li>Competitive packages.</li>\n<li>Room to grow professionally, sponsorship for learning &amp; development of related skills.</li>\n<li>Opportunity to work on a mission that can transform the lives of millions of Vietnamese.</li>\n<li>Annual Performance Bonuses (up to 2 salary months per year).</li>\n<li>Parking fee &amp; Lunch allowance.</li>\n<li>Annual Health Checkup, Premium Health Care (Manager level), Accident Insurance for all members.</li>\n<li>Enjoy a variety of corporate events, from sports competitions, monthly birthday parties, and team building to Year-End Party, etc.</li>\n<li>Flat, open, and fast-paced environment where every idea is welcomed.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
