be explained during the interview.</p>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "dsquare", "job_name": "IT Communicator/ IT Comtor (Japanese N2)", "tag_list": "\nJapanese\n\n\nBridge Engineer\n\n\nGames\n", "location": "54 Hoa Dao, Phu Nhuan, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Upgrade your skills with newest IT technology\nInvolve in top JP advertising agency projects.\nWork in friendly and well supported environment", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><span>DSquare is proud to be a full-service digital advertising house based on a high-technical background.</span></p><p><span>And now, we are proposing an opportunity for IT Communicator to support our client, Hakuhodo Product's, one of the largest promotion production companies, based in Japan.</span></p><p><strong>What will you do?</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Support development team (translate documents; receive, translate requests from Japanese team and communicate for Vietnamese team.) </li>\n<li>Communicate directly with Japanese director, web director to determine their requirements of the project</li>\n<li>Learn, interpret/translate for terminology used in the IT industry</li>\n<li>Read the requirements of the project and pass them on to the development team and translate project specification documents.</li>\n<li>Online meetings with the development team in Vietnam and the development team in Japan to discuss job content, technical solutions, and how to proceed with the project. </li>\n<li>Support to test products.</li>\n<li>Report to the manager.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>Must have:</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Japanese level (JLPT) N2 equivalent or higher</li>\n<li>More than 2 year of experience as IT Communicator.</li>\n<li>Experience in web app development for Japanese offshore projects </li>\n<li>Ability to process information and identify problems quickly</li>\n<li>Good communication skills</li>\n<li>High sense of responsibility, teamwork spirit</li>\n<li>Capable of providing ideas to improve work quality to managers</li>\n</ul><p><strong>Nice to have</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Have a experience as Communicator in Game company </li>\n<li>Have knowledge about Unity or Maya and blender for 3DCG </li>\n<li>Have knowledge about PHP, Javascript, Vuejs</li>\n<li>Experience in XR( AR, VA, MR ) development for Japanese offshore projects</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>▽ We Offer You</strong></p><ul>\n<li>True meaning in your everyday work</li>\n<li>Every month team building party</li>\n<li>14 days of rest and relaxation for each year (P.S. It gets even better over the years!) </li>\n<li>13th-month salary and project-bonus</li>\n<li>Comprehensive social insurance support</li>\n<li>Performance and salary review every year</li>\n<li>Periodical health check-up</li>\n<li>Company trip (every year)</li>\n<li>Transportation allowances for Tet holiday and meal allowances for every lunch </li>\n<li>Wedding, Sickness, Deceased (Parents, Spouse, Children), New Baby Born leaves</li>\n</ul><p><strong>▽ Education</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Self-development training</li>\n<li>Japanese business manner training sessions</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "tpf-vietnam", "job_name": "Data Analyst/Data Engineer (SQL/ASP.NET/C#)", "tag_list": "\nC#\n\n\nSQL\n\n\nData Analyst\n", "location": "Unit D3-1, 3rd floor, Standard Factory D, Lot Va.04b located on Road 24 & 17, Industrial Park within Tan Thuan Export Processing Zone, Tan Thuan Dong Ward, District 7, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "International and proactive working environment\nWell-equipped working condition\nCompetitive salary", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>Developing, maintaining, and troubleshooting systems/projects with team members.</li>\n<li>Designing &amp; developing complex applications.</li>\n<li>Ensuring quality of work through development and implementation of QA procedures and standards.</li>\n<li>Collaborating with other team members in research and use of new technology.</li>\n<li>Optimization system performance and enhance the scalability of systems (Desktop &amp; Web Applications).</li>\n<li>Improving development, testing, and deployment processes in collaboration with Development and Operations teams. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Strong .NET C# web development experience (at least 5+ years).</strong></li>\n<li>Solid experience with ASP.NET MVC (3.x-5.x), ASP.NET Web API, .NET CORE, and related technologies.</li>\n<li>Strong background with MSSQL.</li>\n<li>Core development experience in CMS web and enterprise-scale applications.</li>\n<li>HTML, CSS or one of CSS frameworks Bootstrap 4+, jQuery, JavaScript and AngularJS.</li>\n<li>Good knowledge of OOP design, have applied best practices such as SOLID. Code is clean and well-organized.</li>\n<li>Be a strong team player with a ‘can-do’ attitude and good time management skill;</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>International working environment with young and friendly colleagues</li>\n<li>Great chance to develop your skills and competences, with Inner training and approach new technologies</li>\n<li>Chance to work in Australia</li>\n<li>Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.</li>\n</ul><p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Premium healthcare insurance</li>\n<li>Full social insurance, health insurance, unemployment insurance according to Labor Laws</li>\n<li>13th Bonus Salary</li>\n<li>16 days of annual leave &amp; 06 days of sick leave</li>\n<li>Lunch allowance and free coffee everyday in the office</li>\n<li>Team building activities</li>\n<li>Support sports cost (football, yoga, badminton, ping pong,...)</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "dsquare", "job_name": "Senior Designer for japanese client (UI-UX)", "tag_list": "\nUI-UX\n\n\nDesigner\n", "location": "54 Hoa Dao, Phu Nhuan, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Upgrade your skills with newest IT technology\nInvolve in top JP advertising agency projects.\nWork in friendly and well supported environment", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>・DSquare is proud to be a full-service digital advertising house based on a high-technical background.                         <br>・And now, we are proposing an opportunity for Web designers to support our client, Hakuhodo Product's, one of the largest promotion production companies, based in Japan.                         <br>・We are looking for a Web designer, who can design various websites and web applications to meet with client strict requirements and sometimes will be creative and innovative to create new and fresh pages on mobile and website.                         <br>                        <br><strong>What Will You Do?   </strong>                      <br>・Be in charge of the design process for the website, landing page. (mostly for Japanese client)                         <br>・Work closely with another designer, manager and all team’s members to gather requirements for creating superior, optimised web designs.                         <br>・Translate requirements from clients to design and specifications and assist developers on issues relating to design on daily tasks.                         <br>・Manage own tasks and arrange schedules to handle designs to developers as well as clients on time.                         <br>・Use of judgment to suggest optimal solutions to design problems that balance user needs, business constraints and technological realities.                         <br>・Approach all projects with empathy and emotional design principles.                         <br>・The individual should be comfortable working with senior members of the management team and engineers. You also should be the one who is flexible to adapt to the directive and it is imperative that you have to meet the deadline and specific schedule.                         </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>▽ Must have   </strong>                      <br>・3+ years of web design experience                         <br>・Experience in designing and producing PC and smartphone sites                         <br>・Working knowledge in Adobe Photoshop/Illustrator/XD                         <br>・Ability to successfully manage several projects simultaneously                         <br>・Creation of wire frame (configuration document)                         <br>・Basic web literacy                         <br>・Experience in designing advertising websites such as product brands                         <br>                        <br><strong>▽ Nice to have      </strong>                   <br>・Work experience at a Japanese company as well as experience in Japan type design field.                         <br>・Practical experience with basic HTML / CSS coding                         <br>・Experience customizing CMS such as WordPress                         <br>・SEO knowledge                         <br>・Experience in directing and managing a design team                         <br>・English (or Japanese) basic ability is a must.                         </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>Dsquare is proud to be a full-serviced digital advertising house based on high-technical background. We bring marketing solutions to various brands via touching experiences with users. Through sophisticated working process starting from insightful and logic thinking, Dsquare is where your creativity and innovations blossom.<br><br>The mission to keep community around always well-interacted reminds us keep no member of this house alone here as well. Imagine you are always surrounded by such adorable experts in communication industry.<br> </p><p><strong>▽ We Offer You </strong>                        <br>・True meaning in your everyday work                         <br>・Every month team building party                         <br>・14 days of rest and relaxation for each year (P.S. It gets even better over the years!)                         <br>・13th-month salary and project-bonus                         <br>・Comprehensive social insurance support                         <br>・Performance and salary review every year                         <br>・Periodical health check-up                         <br>・Company trip (every year)                         <br>・Transportation allowances for Tet holiday and meal allowances for every lunch                         <br>・Wedding, Sickness, Deceased (Parents, Spouse, Children), New Baby Born leaves<br>                        <br><strong>▽ Education        </strong>                 <br>・Self-development training                         <br>・Japanese business manner training sessions                         <br>・Opportunities for participating in technical event/seminar</p>\n</div>"}
