{"company_name": "favie-tech", "job_name": "Senior/ Middle FE Angular Developer - Starting ASAP", "tag_list": "\nAngular\n\n\nJavaScript\n\n\nTypeScript\n", "location": "38/6N Nguyễn Văn Trỗi, Phường 15, Phu Nhuan, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Hybrid working environment\nSupport for employee learn more skill\nBonus", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>We are looking for a Front-end Developer to build and implement amazing and complex designs. You will work with other Developers and Product Managers throughout the software development life cycle.</p><p>In this role, you should be a team player with a keen eye for detail, design and problem-solving skills. If you also have experience in HTML, CSS, SCSS, Mixin, Flex, SEO, Javascript, Angular, GraphQL, we’d like to meet you.</p><p>Responsibilities</p><ul>\n<li>Produce clean, efficient, scalable and testable code based on specifications.</li>\n<li>Implement site layout using HTML/CSS.</li>\n<li>Implement site responsiveness.</li>\n<li>Implement site logic using defined technology such as Angular / React.</li>\n<li>Work with REST API to fetch and normalize data from the server.</li>\n<li>Analyze complex design and implement high-quality products.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<h2><strong>Requirements</strong></h2><ul>\n<li>BSc/BA in Computer Science, Engineering or a related field is a plus.</li>\n<li>Basics knowledge with software design and development in a test-driven environment.</li>\n<li>3 - 5years of experience in FE development using SCSS, Angular or related frameworks.</li>\n<li>Have a good grip on API and GraplQI.</li>\n<li>Design patterns, components patterns, Mixin, Design system.</li>\n<li>Knowledge of coding language JavaScript and related frameworks / systems (Angular).</li>\n<li>Ability to learn new languages and technologies.</li>\n<li>Good communication skills - English written is a minimum.</li>\n<li>We will support you in English speaking through training and management.</li>\n<li>Resourcefulness and troubleshooting aptitude.</li>\n<li>Attention to detail - clean and testable code only.</li>\n<li>Strong interpersonal skills, flexibility and strong team spirit.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>Favie is a software development company aiming to build awesome scalable apps for ambitious clients. We work mainly with startups to help them create from scratch their apps, or add new features, or scale for the next level.</p><p>If you are willing to join a very client centric, top quality, dynamic and fun company, you are at the right place.</p>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "favie-tech", "job_name": "Sr Back-end NodeJS Developer", "tag_list": "\nNodeJS\n\n\nPostgreSql\n\n\nJavaScript\n", "location": "38/6N Nguyễn Văn Trỗi, Phường 15, Phu Nhuan, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Hybrid working environment\nSupport for employee learn more skill\nBonus", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>We are looking for a Back-end Developer to build and implement functional programs. You will work with other Developers and Product Managers throughout the software development life cycle.</p><p>In this role, you should be a team player with a keen eye for detail, design and problem-solving skills. If you also have experience in Javascript and using Node.js, Express, GraphQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Firebase or APIs, we’d like to meet you.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Produce clean, efficient, scalable, and testable code based on specifications. </li>\n<li>Work with stakeholders to clarify requirements for your own work. </li>\n<li>Review / Refactor code of team members. </li>\n<li>Analyze complex design and implement high-quality products. </li>\n<li>Help technical leaders to make technical decisions and interview new candidates. </li>\n<li>Coach, train, and support team members.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>+4 years of experience in software development using Node.js or related frameworks / systems. </li>\n<li>SOLID and ACID principles. </li>\n<li>Design patterns: Creational, behavior and structural patterns. </li>\n<li>Very strong technical, analytical and problem solving skills. </li>\n<li>Strong sense of ownership and responsibility for code quality that follows best practices. </li>\n<li>Strong interpersonal skills, flexibility and a strong team spirit. </li>\n<li>Some experience in leading a project or team will be a plus.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>Favie is a software development company aiming to build awesome scalable apps for ambitious clients. We work mainly with startups to help them create from scratch their apps, or add new features, or scale for the next level.</p><p>If you are willing to join a very client centric, top quality, dynamic and fun company, you are at the right place.</p><p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Equipped with Mac Mini/Macbook</li>\n<li>13th month salary, project bonus, quarterly bonus, annual bonus</li>\n<li>Aon Health care insurance</li>\n<li>15 days annual leave/year</li>\n<li>Sponsored online courses fees, technical certification exams</li>\n<li>Company trip, year-end party</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "favie-tech", "job_name": "QA Lead", "tag_list": "\nQA QC\n\n\nTeam Leader\n\n\nTester\n", "location": "38/6N Nguyễn Văn Trỗi, Phường 15, Phu Nhuan, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Hybrid working environment\nSupport for employee learn more skill\nBonus", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>Job brief: </strong></p><ul>\n<li>We are looking for a QA Lead to improve the overall quality of the company deliverables. </li>\n<li>As a QA Lead you will be responsible for defining and implementing the quality strategy as well as leading and mentoring other test engineers. </li>\n<li>You will work closely with Top Management and Technical leaders throughout the software development life cycle to ensure the highest quality product.</li>\n</ul><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Define and implement the company quality standard and procedures</li>\n<li>Build up and mentor the testing team</li>\n<li>Communicate efficiently with management to raise problems and implement solutions</li>\n<li>Drive and develop improved ways of testing, new toolsets, and the best approaches for testing</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li>BSc/BA in Computer Science, Engineering or a related field is a plus. </li>\n<li>Proven experience in both manual and automated testing</li>\n<li>Proven experience in a QA senior position</li>\n<li>Experience in testing web and mobile applications</li>\n<li>Knowledge of automation testing tools</li>\n<li>Knowledge of CI/CD</li>\n<li>Knowledge of testing methodologies</li>\n<li>Knowledge of agile methodologies</li>\n<li>Basics knowledge with software design and development in a test-driven environment. </li>\n<li>Strong English communication skills</li>\n<li>Good leadership skills.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>Favie is a software development company aiming to build awesome scalable apps for ambitious clients. We work mainly with startups to help them create from scratch their apps, or add new features, or scale for the next level.</p><p>If you are willing to join a very client centric, top quality, dynamic and fun company, you are at the right place.</p><p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Equipped with Mac Mini/Macbook</li>\n<li>13th month salary, project bonus, annual bonus</li>\n<li>Aon Health care insurance</li>\n<li>15 days annual leave/year</li>\n<li>Sponsored online courses fees, technical certification exams</li>\n<li>Company trip, year-end party</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "ninja-van-tech-lab", "job_name": "Senior Front-end Engineer (Reactjs/Javascript/HTML)", "tag_list": "\nReactJS\n\n\nJavaScript\n\n\nHTML5\n", "location": "Hado Centrosa Garden, 14-16 Street 7, Ward 12, District 10, Ho Chi Minh", "three_reasons": "Global work environment with flexible working time\nWork with autonomy, no micro-management\nAll your teammates are pros that gets s**t done", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p>Ninja Van is a late-stage logtech startup that is disrupting a massive industry with innovation and cutting edge technology. Launched 2014 in Singapore, we have grown rapidly to become one of Southeast Asia's largest and fastest-growing express logistics companies. Since our inception, we’ve delivered to 100 million different customers across the region with added predictability, flexibility and convenience. Join us in our mission to connect shippers and shoppers across Southeast Asia to a world of new possibilities. </p><p><strong>More about us: </strong></p><p>- We process 250 million API requests and 3TB of data every day.</p><p>- We deliver more than 2 million parcels every day.</p><p>- 100% network coverage with 2600+ hubs and stations in 6 SEA markets (Singapore, Malaysia, Indonesia, Thailand, Vietnam and Philippines), reaching 500 million consumers.</p><p>- 2 Million active shippers in all e-commerce segments, from the largest marketplaces to the individual social commerce sellers.</p><p>- Raised more than US$500 million over five rounds.</p><p>We are looking for world-class talent to join our crack team of engineers, product managers and designers. We want people who are passionate about creating software that makes a difference to the world. We like people who are brimming with ideas and who take initiative rather than wait to be told what to do. We prize team-first mentality, personal responsibility and tenacity to solve hard problems and meet deadlines. As part of a small and lean team, you will have a very direct impact on the success of the company.</p><h3>Role &amp; Responsibilities</h3><ul>\n<li><span>Develop, test and maintain responsive web/mobile apps with elegant UX that delight our users and raise their productivity.</span></li>\n<li><span>Write clean and modular code that you are proud of, with extensibility and performance in mind.</span></li>\n<li><span>Work in cross functional teams with product managers, UX designers and QA engineers to ship software on-quality and on-time.</span></li>\n<li><span>Help level up the team; share knowledge, conduct code and design review; drive code quality and process improvement initiatives.</span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><span><strong>Requirements:</strong></span></p><ul>\n<li><span>4+ years developing HTML5 web apps or hybrid mobile apps, with a proven track record of successfully shipping products.</span></li>\n<li><span>Highly skilled in JavaScript and HTML/CSS.</span></li>\n<li><span>Ability to perform unit testing with frameworks, including Mocha or Jest</span></li>\n<li><span>Strong in ReactJS and Proficiency in building and testing Responsive Single page applications</span></li>\n<li><span>Have experience with Redux and its’ ecosystems</span></li>\n<li><span>Good at Algorithms &amp; Data Structure</span></li>\n<li><span>Good English communication skills.</span></li>\n</ul><p><span><strong>Nice to have: </strong></span></p><ul>\n<li><span>Ability to build NodeJS applications using TypeScript or JavaScript</span></li>\n<li><span>Have experience in UI/UX or building Mobile Apps using React Native</span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><strong>Take charge. </strong>Our flat structure empowers you with the autonomy to find new, inventive solutions.</p><p><strong>Feel your impact. </strong>See your ideas in action as you work them through the challenges of execution.</p><p><strong>Overcome challenges together. </strong>Sometimes things go wrong, but that's okay. Review the work candidly in a safe space, and focus on doing better, together.</p><p><strong>Venture across functions. </strong>Our strong collaborative culture gives you the opportunity to work with and across functions.</p><p><strong>Chart your own career. </strong>Tell us how you'd like to grow, and we'll support you with the training and learning opportunities to design and implement your ideas.</p><p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p><ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Attractive, competitive salary</strong> and incentives.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>13th-month salary</strong> and <strong>yearly performance bonuses up to 4-month salary</strong>.</li>\n<li>Premium healthcare/medical insurance.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Flexible working time</strong>, Monday - Friday.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>MacBook Pro</strong> and extra monitor.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Learning and development programs</strong> and initiatives (Udemy).</li>\n<li>Budget for monthly team-building activities (Weekly Happy Hour, Snack Counter, Team Building Trip, etc.)</li>\n<li>\n<strong>English-speaking</strong> environment.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
{"company_name": "medici", "job_name": "Engineering Director", "tag_list": "\nProject Manager\n\n\nProduct Manager\n", "location": "7th FL, Peakview Tower, 36 Hoang Cau Street, Dong Da, Ha Noi", "three_reasons": "Fast-track career tailored to your strengths\nGrowing your competencies with top experts\nDynamic and diverse environment", "description": "<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><span>Medici is a technology firm endeavoring to provide accessible, trustable and affordable insurance and healthcare service to every Vietnamese. Medici’s ecosystem embraces the entire customers‘ protection and care journey with a nationwide insurance and healthcare partner network over 50 branch offices across more than 40 provinces in Vietnam. Medici has been featured in 2022 Forbes Asia 100 to watch and invested by prestigious regional venture capitals known as Jungle Ventures, Insignia Ventures Partners and Wavemaker Partners.</span></p><p><span>Let‘s look at our numbers:</span></p><ul>\n<li><span>Top 100 to watch Forbes Asia</span></li>\n<li><span>Millions of USD Funding - Series A</span></li>\n<li><span>4 offices, 50 branches nationwide</span></li>\n<li><span>200 employees</span></li>\n<li><span>100+ corporate clients</span></li>\n<li><span>100k+ individual clients</span></li>\n</ul><p><span><strong>WHAT YOU WOULD DO</strong></span></p><p><span>We are seeking an<strong> Engineering Director</strong> <strong>working in Hanoi.</strong></span></p><p><span>As an Engineering Director, you will be responsible for providing guidance, instruction, training, and leadership skills to inspire the team to perform at their optimum.</span></p><ul>\n<li><span>Collaborate with Product Director &amp; cross-functional team to determine Medici product roadmap that aligns with the broader company’s vision</span></li>\n<li><span>Monitor the Medici’s platform structure, be responsible for execution/delivery of projects to achieve the business objectives.  Responsible for the final deliverables and results of all activities regarding the success of the projects.</span></li>\n<li><span>Research on new promising technologies and designing of new features. Monitor reliability and performance of all internal systems to suggest improvements.</span></li>\n<li><span>Manage the team &amp; outsourcing vendors/ contractors through critical projects, making hard tradeoffs between scopes, engineering capacity, and time constraints as well as handle conflicts well and build consensus to meet the progress and quality of the projects. Supervise, assign, review to ensure the quality of application operation execution to achieve outlined goals in development strategy of technical solutions.</span></li>\n<li><span>Supervise, recruit, develop and mentor a team of high-quality engineering talents including Mobile, Front-end and Back-end development teams and their projects.</span></li>\n<li><span>Write and update internal documents with the technical lead.</span></li>\n<li><span>Review technical requirements with technical leads and solution architects. Ensure high quality and completeness of requirements breakdown into tasks</span></li>\n<li><span>Foster agile way of working between tech &amp; product function</span></li>\n<li><span>Demonstrating leadership, management and coordination ability among team members &amp; business owners/ partners.</span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<ul>\n<li><span>A bachelor or postgraduate’s degree in computer science, information technology, engineering or a related field.</span></li>\n<li><span>10+ years professional software development experience for large-scale enterprise software solutions such as fintech, ecommerce, banking, insur-tech &amp; healthtech (plus point)</span></li>\n<li><span>3+ years management experience leading software engineer team (more than 30 members) (must have).</span></li>\n<li><span>Former Head of Engineering, Engineering Director, etc. are preferred.</span></li>\n<li><span>Strong communication, leadership, and problem-solving skills.</span></li>\n<li><span>Track record of managing, recruiting, and retaining talented engineer and develops effective teams.</span></li>\n<li><span>Results-oriented with ability to consistently meet deadlines.</span></li>\n<li><span>A true team player with great interpersonal skills, communicate effectively in both internal and external teams.</span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"job-details__paragraph\">\n<p><span><strong>Considering whether it's worthwhile joining us? Here are the top 4 facts.</strong></span></p><ul>\n<li><span><strong>Fast-track career tailored to your strengths: </strong>Can’t compromise deadlocked processes and conventional career roadmap? We don’t have such things at Medici. You shine. You contribute. You get lifted to your worthy position. Period.</span></li>\n<li>\n<span><strong>Growing your competencies with top experts:</strong> We are a start-up made of veterans: Insurers and techies, marketers and business developers,  </span><span>from the big companies.</span><span> We make sure that you learn best industry practice with the startup speed.</span>\n</li>\n<li><span><strong>Dynamic and diverse environment:</strong> We value diversity and inclusivity. We create a natural habitat for you to thrive as your true self, as long as we work on a vision, you are a part of the team</span></li>\n<li><span><strong>Making social impacts across every move:</strong> Protecting the life of millions, or creating technology initiatives are not stock phrases for us. We are living those words everyday, as we seek to address the complexity of insurance and healthcare in low-tier cities nationwide like Dak Nong, Lai Chau, Con Dao, etc.</span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>"}
